    "created_at": "2014-04-12T01:46:46Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-04-12T01:46:46Z",
    "body": "Note that the assignment like `a = b = ~\"foo\"` (or any other type that moves) will not work as one might expect: the `a = b` part of the assignment would have to move the value out of `b`, leaving it unusable anyway. (The `(a = b) == ...` could theoretically work, since it could be like writing `*({ a = b; &a }) == ...` which will work fine.)\n",
